<paragraph blockId="14.[264,1325,284,670]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis box="[312,414,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[433,588,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolorata">
<emphasis box="[433,588,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">S. bicolorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognised by its coloration. It shares the needlelike paraphyses with 
<emphasis box="[471,588,604,629]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName box="[471,583,604,629]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Scaphoideus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="russus">S. russus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but it has relatively stouter paraphyses that cross over one another.
</paragraph>
